-- Godrej Properties Climbs to Record in Mumbai on Gurgaon Property Agreement
-- Rajhkumar K Shaaw
-- 2010-07-08T04:57:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/godrej-properties-climbs-to-record-in-mumbai-on-gurgaon-property-agreement.html

          
          
             Godrej Properties Ltd., the real
estate company controlled by billionaire Adi Godrej, rose to a
record in Mumbai after it signed an agreement with Frontier Home
Developers Pvt. to develop property in Gurgaon, near New Delhi.  
 Godrej Properties climbed 5 percent to 660.8 rupees, poised
for its highest close since January when the shares were listed.
Godrej Industries Ltd., the biggest shareholder of Godrej
Properties, increased 4.5 percent 175.4 rupees.   
